<h2 id="account-creation-and-login">Account Creation and Log In</h2>

<h3 id="can-not-create-account">The system won't let me create an account! What's wrong?</h3>

<p>First, make sure you've filled out all the fields on the Sign Up page correctly, and that they all say "OK." Note that your username cannot begin with "kraken" even if the system says this is OK. If your username or password are not being accepted as OK, see below for the formatting requirements.</p>

<h3 id="password-format">What are the password format guidelines?</h3>

<p>
</p><ul>
  <li>Minimum length is 8 characters, maximum is 128.</li>
  <li>If the password is less than 25 characters long, it must contain one special character (e.g. !, @, #, $ etc.) and one number.</li>
  <li>If the password is less than 25 characters long, it cannot contain your username.</li>
  <li>If the password is less than 15 characters long, it cannot contain "common" words (e.g. common passwords or names).</li>
  <li>The best passwords are usually <a
      href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Passphrase">passphrases</a> that are easy for you to remember, but hard for others to guess. Famous quotes should be avoided - the best passphrases are usually nonsensical phrases with a few misspelled words, capital letters, numbers, or special characters thrown in (e.g. "figurativ should3#3 Hula-sing" or something like that). We recommend using a password manager such as <a
      href="http://keepass.info/">KeePass</a> to keep your passwords safe from theft or forgetfulness.</li>
</ul>

<p></p>

<p>
  These guidelines are designed to help you create a secure password for the site.
</p>

<h3 id="username-format">What are the username format requirements?</h3>

<p>
</p><ul>
  <li>Cannot begin with "Kraken".</li>
  <li>Minimum 5 characters, maximum 32 characters.</li>
  <li>Only letters (upper and lower case), numbers, '-', '.', and '_' may be used as characters.</li>
</ul>

<p></p>

<h3 id="no-activation-email">I haven't received my account activation email!</h3>

<p>If you haven't received your account activation email, the two most likely reasons are that your email client has put the email in your spam folder, or that you gave us the wrong email during account sign up. Here's a little trouble-shooting guide to help find the problem:</p>
<ol>
  <li>Check your spam folder for an email with the subject "Registration to Kraken."</li>
  <li>If the email isn't in your spam folder, check to see if you entered the wrong email address by trying to create a new account with the email address you think you used before. If you used this address before, the system will let you know there's an account under this email already and won't create the new account for you. If it does let you create the new account, then you entered the wrong email before and you should get an activation email for the new account. If you want to cancel this "test" account and start over, there's a link to cancel in the activation email.</li>
  <li>If trying to create a second account confirms that the first account has the correct email, but you still can't find the activation email for the first account, then try waiting for a while and check your email again. Sometimes it just takes a while for the activation email to arrive.</li>
  <li>If the activation email hasn't arrived after two hours, then you can try creating the account again. If an account isn't activated within two hours of creation, the account cancels and the email associated with it is released.</li>
  <li>If all the steps above fail, contact customer support.</li>
</ol>

<h3 id="cancel-unactivated-account">I've received my activation email, but I want to cancel the account and start over.</h3>

<p>The activation email also contains a link to cancel the account (but it will only cancel if you haven't activated the account already). Cancelling the account will free up the email you used so you can create a different account using the same email.</p>

<h3 id="cannot-login">I can't log into my account!</h3>

<p>If you can't log into your account, this probably means that you're entering the wrong username, password, or two-factor authentication (one-time password). If you get a message saying you've been locked out of your account, please contact customer support.</p>
<ul>
  <li>To get a username reminder, go to Log In &gt; "Forgot Username?" and enter your Kraken account email. Check your email for the username reminder.</li>
  <li>To reset your password, go to Log In &gt; "Forgot Password?" and enter your Kraken account email and username. Check your email for the password reset link.</li>
  <li>To bypass your two-factor authentication (one-time password), go to Log In &gt; "One-time password unavailable?" and enter your Kraken account email and username. Check your email for the bypass code. The login problem may have been caused by your two-factor authentication getting out of sync, so after you gain access to your account, we recommend that you remove your old two-factor authentication and create a new one.</li>
  <li>If you created a <a
      href="#master-key">master key</a>, you will need to enter it for both password reset and two-factor bypass. If you didn't create a master key, just leave the master key field blank.
  </li>
</ul>

<p>If you're having trouble recovering your account, this probably means something is wrong with your login information that you don't expect, so you should carefully follow the complete account recovery steps.</p>

<p>Here are the complete account recovery steps:</p>
<ol>
  <li>If you get a message saying that you've been locked out of your account, please contact customer support before proceeding.</li>
  <li>Verify that you are using the correct username by requesting a username reminder from the Log In page. Click "Forgot Username?" and enter your Kraken email. If you don't get the username reminder email, either you entered the wrong email (it must me the email associated with your Kraken account), or the email may be in your spam folder.</li>
  <li>Reset your password from the Log In page. Click "Forgot Password?" and enter your Kraken account email and username. If you don't get the password reset email, either you entered the wrong information (wrong Kraken email or username), or the reset email may be in your spam folder. Click the reset link and fill in the requested information. If you created a <a
      href="#master-key">master key</a>, you will need to enter it. If you didn't create a master key, just leave the master key field blank. The password reset link expires after 2 hours and can only be used once. However, the password reset link will always appear to work - the form always appears when you click the link, but that doesn't mean it actually worked. You won't know whether its actually worked until you successfully reset the password.
  </li>
  <li>Request a two-factor bypass code from the Log In page. Click "One-time password unavailable?" and enter your Kraken account email, username, and <a
      href="#master-key">master key</a> (if you didn't create a master key, just leave this field blank). If you don't get the bypass email, either you entered the wrong information (wrong email, username, or master key), or the bypass email may be in your spam folder. We recommend that you do this step even if you're sure you didn't create two-factor authentication for your account login. In many cases when users can't log into their account, it's because they've forgotten that they created two-factor authentication. If you don't have two-factor authentication for account login, the bypass email will tell you this.
  </li>
  <li>Finally, log into your account using your verified username, new password, and two-factor bypass code (if needed). If you have two-factor authentication for account login, the login problem may have been caused by your two-factor authentication getting out of sync, so after you gain access to your account, we recommend that you remove your old two-factor authentication and create a new one. If you haven't created a master key yet, we recommend that you do this after you gain access to your account (so it's much harder for someone who has gained access to your email to recover your Kraken login credentials).</li>
</ol>

<p>If, after doing steps 1-5 above, you still cannot access your account, then contact support for further assistance.</p>

<h3 id="cannot-ulock-settings">I can't unlock my account settings!</h3>

<p>If you've locked your account settings but didn't create the <a
    href="#master-key">master key</a> first, the only way to unlock the account is to go to Account &gt; Settings and request an unlock. You will then need to wait for the period of time you set when you locked your settings. The settings lock is an advanced security feature and it cannot be unlocked immediately without the master key. Once your account unlocks, we highly recommend that you create a master key before locking it again.
</p>

