<h3 id="why-deposit-limits">Why are there deposit and withdrawal limits?</h3>

<p>Deposit and withdrawal limits are a required part of our regulatory compliance measures. Please check your deposit limit under Funding &gt; Deposit &gt; (Currency) &gt; "Maximum deposit" before making a deposit. Please do not cut the limit too close since exchange rates can change while your deposit is transferred. You should stay under the limit by at least 5-10% to be safe. Keep in mind that your deposit limit for a currency can be reduced by other deposits or withdrawals, even in other currencies. The funding limits are cumulative across deposits and withdrawals in all currencies.</p>

<h3 id="how-limits-work">How do the deposit and withdrawal limits work?</h3>

<p>The funding limits for a given time period (e.g. day or month) refer to the total amount of deposits and withdrawals in all currencies during that time. The time periods are rolling - e.g. past 24 hours for the daily limit and past 30 days for the monthly limit. The limits are stated in USD, and the amount added toward the limit for non-USD deposits or withdrawals depends on the conversion rate with USD at the time the deposit or withdrawal is made.</p>

<h3 id="deposit-on-hold">Why is my deposit on hold?</h3>

<p>If your deposit is placed on hold, contact customer support to find the reason. Usually it's one of two things:</p>
<ol>
  <li>The deposit takes you over your funding limit. The best way to resolve this situation is to apply for the next higher verification tier to increase your funding limits. The best way to avoid this situation is to monitor your funding limits carefully and stay comfortably under them.</li>
  <li>If you recently made multiple deposits in the same amount, one or more of the deposits may have been put on hold to make sure they aren't part of a duplicate deposit - a single deposit that's been sent to your account multiple times due to a technical issue. The best way to avoid this situation is to send different amounts whenever you send multiple deposits over a short period of time. We recommend sending different amounts for any deposits sent within 5 business days of each other.</li>
</ol>

