<h3 id="what-is-a-position">What is an open position?</h3>

<p>An open position is one that's established using margin, or borrowed funds that are returned to the exchange when the position is closed. Since funds are borrowed to open a position, the profit or loss is unrealized until the position is closed.</p>

<h3 id="what-is-closing-a-position">What is closing a position and how do I do it?</h3>

<p>Closing a position is simply placing an order that is the opposite of the order that opened the position. For instance, if a position was opened with a buy order, a subsequent sell order would be placed to close the position. Once a position is closed, its unrealized profit or loss becomes an actual profit or loss. Clicking on the red box to the right of your open positions listed under the "Positions" tab will bring up an order form for entering a closing order on the position.</p>

<h3 id="how-do-i-select-pairs">How do I select different currency pairs?</h3>

<p>Click the "Currency" field in the upper right of any site page for a list of the pairs that can be selected. You can also select pairs in the intermediate and advanced order forms.</p>

<h3 id="untouched-order">Why is my order "untouched"?</h3>

<p>If the status of your oder is "untouched," this means that it hasn't started to execute yet. This doesn't necessarily mean that there's a problem with the order - it just means that the market conditions required to execute the order haven't appeared yet. If you're expecting the order execute quickly, you should double-check it to make sure it's correct. Consider raising your buy price or lowering your sell price for faster execution.</p>

<h3 id="price-charts">Do you have price charts?</h3>

